cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CC

This paper deals with the fundamental question of characterizing the level of overall privacy degradation in differentially private mechanisms. It involves the use of hypothesis testing and data processing inequalities, which are concepts commonly studied in the areas of cryptography (cs.CR), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of multi-party computation, which falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
